main event: A civilian witness observed a bright, luminous object moving rapidly across the night sky in Roswell, New Mexico on March 8, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as round or oval-shaped, approximately 40-50 feet in diameter, and emitting a pulsating glow.,The object was observed for approximately 30 seconds before disappearing from view.,The sighting was reported to the local police department directly after the observation.,Weather conditions were clear with no clouds during the sighting.,The case was classified as 'Unidentified' due to insufficient conclusive evidence.
sighted object: bright luminous object in the night sky
